   Open in a separate window

   Higher estimated dietary dioxin exposure was seen in younger women and
   in those with higher energy intake, higher alcohol consumption, lower
   pre- and postmenopausal BMI, and in women with 1 or 2 children before
   30 years, with a personal history of benign breast disease and those
   who had breastfed at least one of their children (Table 2).

